-- Raytheon profit rises on military sales
-- 
-- Thu Apr 24, 2008 7:09am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/24/us-raytheon-idUSWNAS938420080424

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Raytheon Co ( RTN.N ) said on Thursday first-quarter profit rose, helped by higher sales of its military and technology gear. 

 The U.S. No. 5 defense contractor reported quarterly profit of $398 million, or 92 cents per share, compared with $346 million, or 76 cents per share, in the year-ago quarter. (Reporting by  Bill Rigby , editing by Mark Porter)